Firſt, of the Independency of the Creator, in producing and diſpoſing of the Creature. Nothing out of God did move him to do any thing to them. True it is, that he knew them in himſelf, in their Cauſes, and in themſelves; not by Species reſulting from them, but by Reflection on his own Nature. Extra ſe non quaerit Lumen ut videat, ipſe enim eſt qui videt & unde videt. He needs not Light from without himſelf to ſee by, for he it is that ſeeth, and from himſelf it is that he ſeeth; as Bernard expreſſeth it. Jer. 5. Before I Formed thee in the Womb, I know thee. 2 Tim. 2.19. The Lord knoweth who are his; 

